7]  Thus,  the  case  in  hand  is  purely  to  decide  whether  impugned  land  is
subjected to a trust or not. To exclude a trust, the attendant circumstances to
be  considered,  where  under  writ  jurisdiction,  it  cannot  be  done  summarily.
Matters in Debt Conciliation Boards are related to loans and debts mainly and
it is hard to consider truth without evidence.  Though, the Board members are
appointed on the section 13 of the Debt Conciliation Ordinance, they deemed to
be public officers as section says1, yet, a writ cannot lie.
